steps.rationale:
Configure in the properties panel:
• HTTP Endpoint → Method: POST
• HTTP Endpoint → URL: "https://api.crm.example.com/customers"
• Payload → Body: ={ email: email, firstName: firstName, lastName: lastName, company: company, leadScore: leadScore, source: "onboarding-flow" }
• Authentication → Bearer token: {{secrets.CRM_API_TOKEN}}
• Output mapping → Result Expression: ={ customerId: response.body.id }

Why: POST bodies are FEEL maps — the whole expression is prefixed with = and the map uses { key: value } syntax (JSON-looking but FEEL). You can reference any variable that's in scope, including leadScore which step 2 just emitted via its Result Expression. Avoid naming any output variable body, url, method, headers, or authentication — those are reserved for the connector's own inputs and would clobber them on the next call.
